<div class="explanation">
  <h2>🔬 Understanding the Concurrency Bug</h2>
  <div class="explanation-grid">
    <div class="explain-block problem">
      <h3>🐛 The Problem — Race Condition</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom:10px">
        Each task reads <code>sharedProgress</code>, adds its chunk, then writes back.
        Because JavaScript's event loop processes microtasks and macrotasks asynchronously,
        multiple tasks can <strong>read the same stale value</strong> before any write completes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Task A reads <code>progress = 30</code></li>
        <li>Task B reads <code>progress = 30</code> (same snapshot!)</li>
        <li>Task A writes <code>progress = 30 + 20 = 50</code></li>
        <li>Task B writes <code>progress = 30 + 25 = 55</code> ← overwrites A!</li>
        <li>Task A's contribution of 20% is <strong>lost</strong></li>
        <li>Final value skips values, goes over 100%, or lands short</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="explain-block solution">
      <h3>✅ The Fix — Accumulated State</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom:10px">
